# =============================================================================
# Plausible CE Postgres Sibling Service - Required Environment Variables
# =============================================================================
# This service uses upstream `postgres:16-alpine` (NOT the Railway
# `postgres-ssl:18` plugin) to avoid the lost+found-initdb crash documented at:
#   .agents/skills/railway-deployment/references/plausible-ce-and-postgres-docker-patterns.md
#   § "Lost+Found Gotcha — Empirically Verified 2026-07-08"
#
# ## PARENT-MOUNT GEOMETRY (CRITICAL)
#
# In the Railway template editor's Volume widget on this Postgres tile, set:
#   Volume name:  postgres-volume (or any name — UI lets you pick)
#   Mount path:   /var/lib/postgresql       <-- parent path on the container
#
# Combined with the PGDATA env var below (= /var/lib/postgresql/data, a SUBPATH of
# the mount), the volume's ext4 `lost+found/` directory lands at:
#   /var/lib/postgresql/lost+found         <-- OUTSIDE PGDATA ✓
#
# initdb only inspects PGDATA (/var/lib/postgresql/data), sees it as empty, and
# creates a fresh cluster. The lost+found directory remains at the volume root
# but never enters PGDATA, so initdb is happy.
#
# DO NOT change PGDATA to a sibling-of-/var/lib/postgresql path (e.g.
# /var/lib/postgresql/data/pgdata) — that would re-introduce the crash.
# DO NOT change the volume mount path to /var/lib/postgresql/data — that would
# trap lost+found INSIDE PGDATA, also crashing initdb.
#
# ## CREDENTIAL SYNCHRONIZATION
#
# Defaults below (postgres / postgres / plausible) MUST stay in sync with
# Plausible CE's DATABASE_URL, which uses the literal form:
#   postgresql://postgres:postgres@postgres.railway.internal:5432/plausible
#
# If a deployer rotates POSTGRES_PASSWORD here (e.g. to a strong random
# secret), they MUST also update Plausible CE's DATABASE_URL to use the new
# password. Two options:
#   A. Hardcode the new password in the Plausible CE tile's DATABASE_URL
#      (inspects in dashboard → Variables → Raw JSON).
#   B. Use Railway variable references:
#        DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres:${{POSTGRES_PASSWORD}}@${{RAILWAY_PRIVATE_DOMAIN}}:5432/plausible
#      (Note: depends on sibling service's PRIVATE_DOMAIN resolving at deploy time.)
#
# ## OPTIONAL CUSTOMIZATION
#
# Uncomment / override any of the lines below to change the default behavior.

# --- Default values (literal — match Plausible CE's DATABASE_URL out of the box) ---

POSTGRES_USER=postgres
POSTGRES_PASSWORD=postgres
POSTGRES_DB=plausible

# --- Required: PGDATA must be a subpath of the volume mount path /var/lib/postgresql ---

PGDATA=/var/lib/postgresql/data

# --- Optional: Connection limits / tuning (uncomment to override) ---

# Maximum concurrent connections (default 100)
# MAX_CONNECTIONS=200

# Shared buffers size (default 128MB)
# SHARED_BUFFERS=256MB

# --- Optional: Replication (not enabled by default) ---

# Replication user/pass — leave commented unless you set up streaming replication
# POSTGRES_REPLICATION_USER=replicator
# POSTGRES_REPLICATION_PASSWORD=replace-with-strong-password
